stork.feather

Class ProxyElement<S extends Resource,D extends Resource>

  • java.lang.Object
    • stork.feather.ProxyElement<S,D>
  • Type Parameters:
    S - The source Resource type.
    D - The destination Resource type.
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Sink, Tap

    public abstract class ProxyElement<S extends Resource,D extends Resource>
extends Object
    An abstract base class for anything which can serve as an element in a proxy transfer pipeline. In particular, this is the base class for Sink and Tap.

      • drain

        protected abstract void drain(Slice slice)
        Drain a Slice through the pipeline. This method returns as soon as possible, with the actual I/O operation taking place asynchronously.
        Parameters:
        slice - a Slice being drained through the pipeline.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if this method is called when the pipeline has not been initialized.

      • start

        protected abstract void start(Bell bell)
                       throws Exception
        Prepare to begin the transfer of data. This involves, for example, establishing data channels, pipelining transfer commands, altering state, etc. The Sink will ring bell when data may begin being drained.
        Parameters:
        bell - a Bell whose ringing indicates the transfer of data may begin.
        Throws:
        Exception - if this transfer element cannot be started for a reason known immediately.

      • finish

        protected abstract void finish()
        Finish the flow of data.

      • pause

        protected abstract void pause(Bell bell)
        Pause the transfer until Bell is rung. When this is called, data should no longer be drained through the pipeline, and the attached Tap should cease reading from underlying data buffers. The Sink will ring bell when the transfer of data may be resumed.
        Parameters:
        bell - the Bell whose ringing indicates that the transfer of data may resume.

      • close

        protected void close()
              throws Exception
        Free any system resources allocated by this transfer element. This will be called after the transfer element has finished transferring data. Subclasses should implement this to free any resources if any are allocated.
        Throws:
        Exception - Any Exception thrown by this method is ignored.
